      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOONGALLA GHOST (2) was safely held in tougher company last start at this track, but prior to that won by one length at this track (30.19) beating Bit Of Potash in a Grade 5 on April 22. Key runner on her best form. WINDORAH (8) charged out of the boxes with a strong early split and went straight to the front, scoring an all the way win (30.32) over 525m at this track. Some good form is emerging from her last run. One of the leading chances again. ARCHER SWEET (5) settled off speed and overcame a collision with another runner to work home into the placings when second (30.53) at this track in a Grade 5. Rates a leading chance. ASTON MORENO (7) cannot be dismissed although new to this venue.",
